content.text:
Let me analyze the two structures shown in the main target image and provide assembly instructions for both.

Structure 1 (Left structure - Tower with orange roof):
This is a vertical structure with:
- 4 layers
- Orange cylindrical pillars in the middle
- Yellow rectangular base and platform
- Blue and red walls on top
- Orange triangular roof

Structure 2 (Right structure - Red arches with yellow platform):
This is a horizontal structure with:
- 3 layers
- Red arch components at the bottom
- Yellow rectangular platforms
- Red walls and roof on top

Let me provide the assembly sequence for both structures:

For Structure 1 (Tower):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 9 (bottom yellow base)
    Step2: Move block with index 11 (left orange cylinder)
    Step3: Move block with index 12 (right orange cylinder)
    Step4: Move block with index 10 (yellow platform)
    Step5: Move block with index 7 (left blue block)
    Step6: Move block with index 6 (red center block)
    Step7: Move block with index 8 (right blue block)
    Step8: Move block with index 14 (roof triangle)
}

For Structure 2 (Arches):
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1 (left red arch)
    Step2: Move block with index 2 (right red arch)
    Step3: Move block with index 9 (left yellow platform)
    Step4: Move block with index 10 (right yellow platform)
    Step5: Move block with index 6 (left red block)
    Step6: Move block with index 6 (right red block)
    Step7: Move block with index 15 (roof triangle)
}
